         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1804-05-17.04" n="">
            <sp who="jo">
               <speaker>Ordway</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date/>
               </ab>
               <p>
Thursday May 17th 1804, a fair day, but Rainy night, nothing occured worthy of notice this day

</p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1804-05-17.05" n="">
            <sp who="cf">
               <speaker>Floyd</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date/>
               </ab>
               <p>
Thursday may 17th 1804    a fair but Rainey Night



</p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1804-05-17.06" n="">
            <sp who="jw">
               <speaker>Whitehouse</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date/>
               </ab>
               <p>
Thursday 17th May 1804.    a pleasant morning.    we are waiting here the arival of <name type="person" key="Lewis, Meriwether">Capt. Lewis</name>.    the evening rainy.</p>
               <p>
Thursday May 17th    A pleasant morning.    We are still here waiting the arrival of <name type="person" key="Lewis, Meriwether">Captain Lewis</name>; in the Evening we had some Rain.—

</p>
            </sp>
         </div>
